<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="800" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/7879: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-07T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            7, 1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>1. Disregard Department’s 106, December 30, 1 p.m.<note n="56" xml:id="d800fn56">Not printed.</note></p>
                            <p>Force Commander European waters, London, has instructions to keep
                                vessel within easy sailing distance.</p>
                            <p>Keep Department and also Embassy London fully informed.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>